&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;FLSA Classification: &lt;/strong&gt;Exempt&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary Range: &lt;/strong&gt;$180,000 - $200,000 plus bonus &amp;amp; stock options&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reports to: &lt;/strong&gt;SVP, Corporate Finance&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: &lt;/strong&gt;Brooklyn, NY (Hybrid)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About The Company:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NineDot&#39;s name derives from the&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.artofplay.com/blogs/articles/history-of-the-nine-dot-problem&quot;&gt; classic mathematical puzzle&lt;/a&gt; for sparking out-of-the-box solutions. As a leading community-scale, clean energy developer with a growing portfolio of projects across a range of technologies, NineDot Energy is creating innovative energy solutions that support a more resilient electric grid, deliver economic savings, address environmental justice and reduce carbon emissions. We plan to develop, build and operate more than 400 MW of clean energy systems by 2026 that will strengthen the local power grid infrastructure and provide clean, reliable and resilient power to tens of thousands of New York households and businesses. This is all in support of New York State’s mission to achieve 100% clean energy by 2040.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With the backing of Manulife Investment Management and The Carlyle Group - two of the world’s leading infrastructure investors - NineDot is continuing to expand its core battery energy storage pipeline, deliver enhanced products and services, explore new regions and consider potential acquisitions all to advance the decarbonization of New York’s grid. This is an exciting opportunity to build a platform from the ground-up with a world-class team of developers and innovators.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an experienced Controller to lead the Company&#39;s accounting function and support the continued growth of our clean energy platform. Reporting to the SVP, Corporate Finance, the Controller will oversee corporate and project accounting, financial reporting, month-end close, internal controls, and accounting operations across a growing portfolio of renewable energy assets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Controller will play a critical role in ensuring the integrity of financial reporting, supporting project development and financing activities, and building scalable accounting processes to support the Company&#39;s growth. This individual will partner closely with Project Finance, FP&amp;amp;A, Tax &amp;amp; Treasury, Project Development, Engineering &amp;amp; Construction, Asset Operations, Legal, and external stakeholders while leading and developing a high-performing accounting team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate is a hands-on accounting leader with strong technical expertise, experience managing complex project-based accounting environments, and a passion for building processes, systems, and teams in a fast-growing organization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Accounting Operations &amp;amp; Financial Reporting&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead all aspects of corporate and project accounting, ensuring accurate and timely financial reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee monthly, quarterly, and annual close processes and continuously improve close efficiency and effectiveness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure compliance with U.S. GAAP and other applicable accounting standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead preparation and review financial statements and supporting analyses for management, lenders, investors, and external stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and enhance accounting policies, procedures, and documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Technical Accounting, Controls &amp;amp; Audit&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accounting policies and procedures across all legal entities.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
